examples.en: The new year draws near.
The end draws nigh.
He draws beautifully.
This chimney draws very well.
The band always draws a large crowd.
Winter draws nigh (=will start soon).
The college draws students from around the world.
The play still draws.
The chimney draws well.
This boat draws 70 inches.
The deadline draws ever closer.
The rod draws the electricity from the air.
The first quarter of 2006 draws to a close.
...night draws on, so we should hurry home...
Congreve draws a debauched aristocratic society.
He draws all the trumps and wins all the tricks.
Plenty of money often draws out the worst in people.
Plato draws all the strands of the argument together.
He has an indefinable quality that draws people to him.
The writer draws comparisons between the two presidents.
His work draws heavily on learning theories of the 1980s.
She draws spiritual sustenance from daily church attendance.
The report draws a distinction between various forms of health care.
The author draws a comparison between East and West Germany and the North-South divide in England.
